data.description:
Made mainly for the developers, but also for those, who want to see what their Pebble Time can show.
This app mixes two basic colors into 50% mix. Top button select Red, middle Green and the bottom one selects Blue. Longer push of the middle button switches between top and left colors. 

If you want to insert resulting color in your code, you use the numbers in the top left corner like (GColor8){ .argb = number1 } and (GColor8){ .argb = number2 }
If you want to mix them, you can use the great Simple Dithering Library by Mathew Reiss:
draw_dithered_rect(ctx, GRect(...),(GColor8){ .argb = number1 },(GColor8){ .argb = number2 },DITHER_50_PERCENT);

